14/10/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu appointed Dacian Ciolos as Romania's new agriculture minister on Friday (October 12th). Ciolos succeeds Decebal Traian Remes, who stepped down on Thursday amid a major corruption scandal. Ciolos, 37, previously served as deputy minister of agriculture. The government describes him as an expert on farm issues with solid experience in relations with EU institutions. (Xinhua - 13/10/07; Hotnews.ro, Rompres, AP, Thomson Financial - 12/10/07)
